# Cline/Claude Code Rules for Local AI Project

## Git Configuration
- Always use git user: "utfcmac" with email "utfcmac@users.noreply.github.com"
- Git hooks are installed automatically and will check/fix this for you
- If hooks prompt you, respond appropriately to fix issues
- Before any git operations, verify user config: `git config user.name` and `git config user.email`
- If user is not "utfcmac", run: `git config user.name "utfcmac" && git config user.email "utfcmac@users.noreply.github.com"`

## Git Hooks (Automated Checks)
- Pre-commit hook checks for unstaged files - RESPOND TO PROMPTS
- Pre-commit hook verifies git user - will auto-fix if you confirm
- Commit-msg hook validates conventional commit format - will reject bad messages
- To bypass hooks: `git commit --no-verify` (only in emergencies!)

## Commit Message Convention
- MUST follow Conventional Commits format: `<type>(<scope>): <subject>`
- Valid types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, chore
- Examples:
  - `feat(api): add language parameter to generate endpoint`
  - `fix(dashboard): correct memory calculation`
  - `docs(readme): update installation instructions`
  - `chore(deps): update next-intl to v4.9.0`

## CHANGELOG Management
- ALWAYS update CHANGELOG.md when making changes
- Add changes under `[Unreleased]` section
- Follow Keep a Changelog format with sections: Added, Changed, Deprecated, Removed, Fixed, Security
- When creating a release, move `[Unreleased]` content to new version section with date

## Development Workflow
1. Make code changes
2. Update CHANGELOG.md under `[Unreleased]`
3. Test locally: `npm run build && npm run start:standalone`
4. Commit with conventional commit message
5. Push to GitHub: `git push origin main`

## Release Workflow
1. Update CHANGELOG.md: change `[Unreleased]` to `[X.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD`
2. Commit: `git commit -m "chore(release): prepare vX.Y.Z"`
3. Create annotated tag: `git tag -a vX.Y.Z -m "Release vX.Y.Z: Brief description"`
4. Push with tags: `git push origin main --tags`
5. GitHub Actions will automatically create the release

## Versioning (Semantic Versioning)
- MAJOR (X.0.0): Breaking changes (API incompatible changes)
- MINOR (0.X.0): New features (backward compatible)
- PATCH (0.0.X): Bug fixes (backward compatible)

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Prefer functional components in React
- Use async/await over promises
- Add JSDoc comments for exported functions
- Keep functions small and focused
- Use meaningful variable names

## i18n (Internationalization)
- When adding new UI text, ALWAYS add translations to both:
  - `src/messages/de.json`
  - `src/messages/en.json`
- Use `useTranslations()` in client components
- Use `getTranslations()` in server components

## API Development
- Always validate API key with `validateApiKey(request)`
- Return consistent error format: `{ success: false, error: "message" }`
- Log all generations to SQLite via `insertGeneration()`
- Support optional `language` parameter (default: "de")

## Testing Requirements
- Build must succeed: `npm run build`
- Test standalone server: `npm run start:standalone`
- Test API endpoints with curl
- Verify dashboard at http://localhost:3100

## File Organization
- API routes: `src/app/api/*/route.ts`
- Components: `src/components/`
- UI components: `src/components/ui/` (shadcn/ui)
- Utilities: `src/lib/`
- Translations: `src/messages/`

## Documentation
- Update README.md when adding features or changing APIs
- Update CONTRIBUTING.md if development workflow changes
- Add JSDoc comments to complex functions

## Dependencies
- Use `npm install` (not yarn or pnpm)
- Update package.json AND package-lock.json
- Document breaking dependency changes in CHANGELOG

## Build System
- Never hardcode paths - use dynamic resolution
- Post-build script automatically copies assets
- Standalone build must work on any machine/path

## Security
- Never commit `.env.local` or API keys
- Validate all API inputs
- Use API key authentication for protected endpoints
- Document security changes in CHANGELOG under "Security" section

## When Creating PRs (for external contributors)
- Fill out PR template completely
- Link related issues
- Update CHANGELOG.md
- Ensure CI passes
- Use conventional commit messages

## Error Handling
- Always wrap async operations in try/catch
- Log errors with context
- Return user-friendly error messages
- Update generation status in database on error

## Performance
- Monitor process memory usage
- Use dynamic imports where appropriate
- Optimize database queries
- Cache Ollama responses when applicable

## Remember
- Git user MUST be "utfcmac"
- ALWAYS update CHANGELOG.md
- ALWAYS use conventional commits
- ALWAYS test build before pushing
- Releases are AUTOMATED via tags
